Learning the art of prayer is not an everyday dinner table discussion. In fact, it‚Äôs rarely a discussion at all. Prayer was most likely by way of a directive from a parent or grandparent. Prayer may have been observed but not understood. You just positioned yourself in the act of it to avoid any repercussions that came from not obeying your elder.

So You Think You Can Pray is written words from encounters with my communication with God. These expressions were witnesses to my personal elevation in the realms where God directly communicated with me. It is here where I was molded, reshaped, and delivered from who and where I was spiritually to where God wants me to go. It was here I received my life lessons to share with others and to continue to be under the covenant of God to serve as a vehicle to bring awareness to learn and understand the beauty of prayer. We all journey through life. We have a birth date, and an expiration date. What are you doing with your in between time? Are you grateful for the air you breathe or are you the one who constantly complains? Life happens. Time cannot be bought or returned. How are you utilizing your time? Be grateful . Appreciate the small things. Develop a relationship with God. Embrace his presence. Learn to rejoice in God‚Äôs grace and mercy.

‚ÄúRejoice always. Pray without ceasing and in everything give thanks for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus for you.‚Äù 1 Thessalonians 5:16‚Äì18.
